 sources are re-edited from manuscripts closer toChaucer's copies. Volume I includes chapters on the Frame and the tales of the Reeve, Cook, Friar, Clerk, Squire, Franklin, Pardoner, Melibee, Monk, Nun's Priest, Second Nun and Parson. Chapters on the other tales, together with the General Prologue and Retractions will appear in Volume II.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aComparative literaturexThemes, motives. 0aLiterature, MedievalxThemes, motives. 0aLiterature, Medieval. 4aMedieval Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh1 aAskins, William R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeidler, Peter G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBestul, Thomas H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooper, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorreale, Robert ., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDiMarco, Vincent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, Robert R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarrell, Thomas J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodwin, Amy W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHamel, Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHamel, Mary, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNewhauser, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNicholson, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReames, Sherry L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScattergood, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWheatley, Edward,